  {
    "title": "Ban/Pick Phase",
    "depth": 0,
    "paragraphs": [
      {
        "sentences": [
          {
            "text": "It is advised to pick EXP laner after enemy's pick, so that you are guaranteed at least an equal opponent in lane."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "title": "Rotation Tips",
    "depth": 0,
    "paragraphs": [
      {
        "sentences": [
          {
            "text": "Minions in EXP lane will give 25% more EXP than other lanes in the first 5 minutes."
          },
          {
            "text": "Try to reach level 4 as soon as possible before the first Turtle, as it will certainly spawn next to EXP lane."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "title": "Gameplay",
    "depth": 0
  },
  {
    "title": "First 2 minutes",
    "depth": 1,
    "paragraphs": [
      {
        "sentences": [
          {
            "text": "Some heroes can perform lane cutting, but it is advised to avoid dying, so that your teammates do not have to divide focus on EXP lane early on.",
            "links": [
              {
                "text": "lane cutting",
                "type": "internal",
                "page": "lane cutting"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "sentences": [
          {
            "text": "Before the first Turtle, your midlaner might come and you may want to share the fourth minion wave with them, as the 25% exp bonus means both of you will reach level 4 and have ultimates available for contesting turtle."
          },
          {
            "text": "If you are already at level 4, give up the minions for the midlaner."
          },
          {
            "text": "The Exp Laners role in contesting the turtle is zoning if you are playing heroes like ,,,,,,, and and pick off the enemy jungler if you’re playing heroes like ,,, , and."
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
